## Summary Table

| Phase | Workers affected | What changes | New API needed? | Backward compatible? |
|-------|-----------------|--------------|-----------------|----------------------|
| 1 | All | Abstraction layer + constructor injection | No | Yes — local mode unchanged |
| 2 | VisionWorker, EmbedWorker | `abs_path()` → `read_artifact()` + temp file | No | Yes |
| 3 | ProxyWorker | `storage.write()` → `write_artifact()` | No | Yes |
| 4 | VideoPreviewWorker | ffmpeg → tmp → `write_artifact()` | No | Yes |
| 5a | Server only | Add `scene_rep` artifact type | Yes — upload endpoint | Yes |
| 5b | VideoIndexWorker, VideoVisionWorker | All storage calls → `artifact_store` | No (Phase 5a provides it) | Yes |

After all phases, a worker running on a client machine with no access to the server's `DATA_DIR`
can process every job type. Source file access (RAW decoding, EXIF extraction, video transcoding)
remains local — no source files are transmitted to the server. The existing single-host deployment
is unchanged throughout.
